UNTIL THIS FILE CONTAINS A REAL LICENSE.

The license is an open decision. Apache-2.0 is the leaning default and the
recommended choice for an adoption-first launch (permissive, includes a patent
grant, enterprise-friendly). AGPL-3.0 is the alternative if protecting a hosted
commercial offering takes priority over adoption.

To finalize:
  - Apache-2.0:  drop in the standard Apache License 2.0 text and add a NOTICE
                 file. Adopt a DCO (Signed-off-by) for contributions so future
                 major versions can be relicensed if needed.
  - AGPL-3.0:    drop in the standard GNU AGPLv3 text. Plan for a CLA if you
                 intend to relicense for the commercial product.

Then update the License badge and License section in README.md.

See docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-21-open-source-launch-readiness-design.md, section 5.
